org.dockbox.hartshorn.api.events.processing

Class AbstractEventParamProcessor<A extends java.lang.annotation.Annotation>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.dockbox.hartshorn.api.events.processing.AbstractEventParamProcessor<A>
  • Type Parameters:
    A - The annotation type the processor applies to.

    public abstract class AbstractEventParamProcessor<A extends java.lang.annotation.Annotation>
extends java.lang.Object
    A low level type used to process a given Annotation type. Typically this is only used by EventWrapper implementations to populate, filter, or skip parameter arguments.

      • process

        @Nullable
public abstract @Nullable java.lang.Object process(@Nullable
                                                              @Nullable java.lang.Object object,
                                                              A annotation,
                                                              Event event,
                                                              java.lang.reflect.Parameter parameter,
                                                              EventWrapper wrapper)
                                                       throws SkipEventException
        Processes the given object based on available information in the given Annotation, Event, Parameter} and/or EventWrapper. If the parameter does not meet expectations, or should not be used in a given listener method, SkipEventException is thrown.
        Parameters:
        object - The object to process.
        annotation - The annotation containing the definition of how the processor should act.
        event - The event for which the listener can be invoked.
        parameter - The parameter on which the annotation is applied.
        wrapper - The EventWrapper which contains the invoking definition.
        Returns:
        The processed object
        Throws:
        SkipEventException - Indicates the event listener should be skipped.
